{"TopicId":161984,"ForumId":16,"TopicTitle":"No drag from Mk3 Ramp","CreatedByName":"*MajorTom*","CreatedById":144002,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-12T13:22:11Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"*MajorTom*","CreatedById":144002,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-12T13:22:11Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nis it normal or just aerodynamics bug? (still have 1.2.2, but looks like it present in 1.3)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u00222b320ffe2b84.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022576\u0022 src=\u0022http://s012.radikal.ru/i320/1706/4d/2b320ffe2b84.jpg\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"bewing","CreatedById":154251,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-12T16:02:37Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI think what you mean instead of \u0022drag\u0022 is directional lift.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThose MK3 parts are considered lifting surfaces. Lifting surfaces are defined to be symmetrical. So as long as you are following prograde, there will be no lift in one direction or another.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere is drag on the part that pushes backwards.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DrLicor","CreatedById":165712,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-12T23:55:09Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAs \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/154251-bewing/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022154251\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/154251-bewing/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@bewing\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0explained the stock aerodynamics of Ksp, there\u0027s a mod that does correct that: \u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/19321-122-ferram-aerospace-research-v01581-lewis-6417-better-late-than-never-edition/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Ferram Aerospace Research (mod)\u0022\u003EFAR\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHowever, this mod is not up to date for 1.3.x as far as I know.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Spricigo","CreatedById":166502,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-13T02:47:46Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223089151\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022161984\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221497283357\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022154251\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022bewing\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n10 hours ago, bewing said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo as long as you are following prograde, there will be no lift in one direction or another.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nStill seems to be lots of drag in front of \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECoM\u003C/abbr\u003E. The kind of vessel that flips with a hair of deviation from prograde. \u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nVery strange, \u00A0to say the least.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}